Reference:
  - Title: Qur’ân
    Locus: XVII 72
---
The greatest calamity that befalls the heedless is that they are ignorant of
their own faults： for anyone who is ignorant here shall also be ignorant
hereafter： 'Those who are blind in this world shall be blind in the next
world'.
